  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0dba \u0dab\u0dba \u0dba\u0db1\u0dd4 \u0dab\u0dba \u0d9a\u0db4\u0dcf \u0dc4\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A non-performing loan is not a write-off",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The People's Bank says that non-performing loans are loans that have not been properly paid principal or interest for a specified period of time, and this is not a write-off of the loan in any way.",
        "Taking into account the talk spread in the society in recent days regarding the non-performing asset (loan) portfolio (NPP) of the People's Bank, the bank has explained the facts as follows.",
        "People's Bank points out that when a loan is classified as a non-performing asset, the bank initiates a recovery process that includes actions such as follow-up, negotiation, auction and litigation. Accordingly,",
        "1. A debt write-off is done only if all possible avenues for its recovery have been completely exhausted.",
        "2. The bank's non-performing asset (loan) portfolio consists of various credit facilities granted over the past two decades.",
        "3. None of the loans discussed in the media in recent days have been written off.",
        "Accordingly, the percentage of non-performing assets of the People's Bank in the country's banking system is in a positive state, and as a responsible financial service provider that provides unparalleled protection for its customers' deposits, the People's Bank considers recovery of non-performing assets as its top priority."
      ],
